overview:
@TechnologyRootOverviewIf your documentation only consists of articles, without any framework documentation or other top-level pages, DocC will use the only article or the article with the same base name as the documentation catalog (’.docc’ directory) as the top-level page. If the documentation doesn’t contain an article with the same base name as the documentation catalog, DocC will synthesize a minimal top-level page.

To customize which article is the top-level page of your documentation, add a TechnologyRoot directive within a Metadata directive in that article:

# Page Title


@Metadata {
   @TechnologyRoot
}
